**Step 3: Check your branch history.**

```bash
git log --oneline --graph --all
```

The `--all` flag shows ALL branches. You should see `main` at your old commit and `phase-0-practice` three commits ahead. They
have **diverged** — `main` is stable, your branch has new work.

**Step 4: Push the branch to GitHub.**

```bash
git push origin phase-0-practice
```

This creates the branch on GitHub. Your local branch now has a remote counterpart.

**Step 5: Open a Pull Request on GitHub.**

1. Go to `github.com/YOURUSERNAME/achilles`
2. GitHub will show a banner: "phase-0-practice had recent pushes — Compare & pull request"
3. Click it
4. Fill in the PR:
